<h1>Introduction</h1>

<p>The Fire Druid is known for being very strong in the early and mid game but running into a lot of Fire Immune monsters in Hell. That being said, he can be extremely strong in targeted farming of areas with few Fire Immune Monsters and overall still has great Damage output to beat the game.</p>

<h1>Quick Reference</h1>

<h2>Skill Build</h2>

<p>The following section shows the core skills for the Fire Druid. For a detailed breakdown of all core and optional skills as well as the recommended order for allocating skill points, refer to the Skills section of this guide.</p>

<ol>
<li>1 point to all prerequisites</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Fissure@@@ - Invest immediately. This is your main Damage skill, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Firestorm@@@ - Main Damage until @@@D2Fissure@@@. @@@D2Fissure@@@ Synergy, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Volcano@@@ - Synergy for @@@D2Fissure@@@ and decent Single Target Damage against monsters like Baal who do not move much, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2OakSage@@@ - Big Increase in Life, required</li>
</ol>

